author: Lee Kah Leng
title: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro price leaked ahead of local launch - Tech News | The Star Online
text:
Thursday, 23 February 2017 | MYT 1:21 PM Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro price leaked ahead of local launch by lee kah leng Attractive offering: The C9 Pro is an upper mid-range device with a large 6in display. — Samsung 
If the latest leak is proven to be true, Malaysians will soon see yet another Galaxy smartphone go on sale here in the form of the C9 Pro. 
According to Technave , a recent Samsung dealer's event apparently revealed that the C9 Pro is expected to be priced at RM2,299, putting it in the upper mid-range segment between the flagship S and the mid-range A series. The presentation slide which supposedly confirmed the price of the upcoming Galaxy C9 Pro. — TechNave 
The C9 Pro is a phablet which was originally released for the China market, sporting a 6in full-HD Super Amoled display. 
Both the rear and front facing cameras are rated at 16-megapixel with large f /1.9 aperture for better low light photography. 
Other specs include an octa-core 1.9GHz processor, 64GB internal storage and a large 4,000mAh battery, according to the Technave post. 
It’s interesting to note that the C9 Pro’s 6GB RAM is thus far the largest amount of memory offered in a Samsung smartphone in the local market 
To date, no timeline for release has been revealed yet but based on the leaks and SIRIM database entry, the next Galaxy might be coming as early as March 2017. Related Stories
